task.summary: Configure Maven to build project and make an executable jar package Add two idea configuration, a maven one which call maven packaging, and executable one to launch or debug the app, with maven build as dependency.
Add more or less all needed dependencies (except for graphics) and plays a little bit with Javax validations and Lombok code generator.

Add a window interface, allowing us to define some window controller, able to be launch and to take a state. Add some placeholder class such as State, GUIController, ConsoleController and WindowFactory. Checking if an arguments is passed as parameter, and creating correct window controller from this.
Think I globally conceived the main loop and interaction between window controller and game logic.
Now able to create a player, with a name and origin
Begin the inventory system with equip.
Create JSONObject from State and all subclasses

Delete everything and starting fresh. Add GameController, directly construct from the program argument. Also make main a lot prettier by making my own exception, with a custom to String, and catching it to print usage in this unique case of invalid argument passed.
Use Jackson and successfully deserialize items.json
